AI-Powered Test Case Generation Skill — Implementation Plan

Version: 1.0
Created: 2026-06-04
Status: Draft (Phase 1 MVP)

==============================================================================
EXECUTIVE SUMMARY
==============================================================================

This plan defines the architecture, implementation phases, and roadmap for building
an AI-powered Test Case Generation skill that converts requirements specifications
into deterministic, traceable automation-ready test artifacts.

The skill prioritizes:
- Determinism: identical inputs → identical outputs
- Modularity: framework adapters pluggable without core redesign
- Traceability: every test maps back to source requirement
- Anti-hallucination: no invented fields or endpoints
- Extensibility: new frameworks and formats without architectural change

==============================================================================
DESIGN VISION
==============================================================================

Core Promise
"From specification to automation in one deterministic pass, with full traceability
and zero hallucinated requirements."

Constraints
- No external YAML or JSON libraries (Python 3.9+ std lib only, or minimal deps)
- File-based Phase 1 (no HTTP API; no CLI framework overhead)
- Pure Python core; rendering adapters handle framework-specific syntax
- 100% deterministic output given same source + config + generator version

Design Goals
✓ Deterministic      — Reproducible outputs; strong canonicalization of sources
✓ Modular            — Clean separation: parse → normalize → generate → render
✓ Traceable          — Every test artifact maps to one or more requirement IDs
✓ Framework Agnostic — Gherkin, Playwright, JUnit, REST Assured via adapters
✓ Extensible         — Add new framework adapter without touching core generator
✓ Anti-hallucination — Strict adherence to source specifications; gaps reported
✓ Flexible Inputs    — Works with or without OpenAPI (skip API tests if no contract provided)
✓ Testable           — Unit tests for each component; integration tests for flows

==============================================================================
PHASE 1: MVP COMPONENTS (Weeks 1–4)
==============================================================================

1. Requirement Analyzer
   Input: Markdown user stories + acceptance criteria
   Output: Canonicalized requirement model
   
   Responsibilities:
   - Parse markdown for user story format (As a <actor>, I want <action>, so <benefit>)
   - Extract acceptance criteria and map IDs (AC-NNN)
   - Identify business rules, preconditions, postconditions
   - Normalize requirement IDs (generate if missing)
   - Detect and flag ambiguous language ("may", "should", "order to")
   
   Key Methods:
   - parse_markdown_story(path) -> Story
   - extract_acceptance_criteria(text) -> Requirement[]
   - identify_business_rules(text) -> Rule[]
   - canonicalize_requirement_id(text) -> str

2. API Contract Analyzer [OPTIONAL COMPONENT]
   Input: OpenAPI 3.x YAML/JSON (optional)
   Output: Canonicalized API endpoint model
   Activation: Conditional — runs only if OpenAPI spec file is provided in config
   
   Responsibilities (if enabled):
   - Parse OpenAPI 3.x spec (dereference $ref)
   - Extract endpoints, methods, request/response schemas
   - Derive field constraints from JSON Schema (type, format, minLength, minimum, enum)
   - Map status codes and response payloads
   - Flag incomplete specs (missing request schema, response definitions)
   
   Behavior (if disabled):
   - Skip this component entirely
   - Do not invent API contracts from acceptance criteria
   - Downstream generators skip API Contract test generation
   - Coverage report excludes API metrics
   
   Key Methods:
   - parse_openapi(path) -> ApiSpec (or None if disabled)
   - extract_endpoints(spec) -> Endpoint[]
   - extract_field_constraints(schema) -> Constraint[]
   - normalize_status_code(code) -> int

3. Test Design Generator
   Input: Requirement[], [optional] ApiSpec, Constraint[]
   Output: TestCase[]
   
   Responsibilities:
   - For each acceptance criterion, generate:
     ✓ 1 positive test (happy path, valid inputs)
     ✓ 1 negative test (missing required, invalid type, constraint violation)
     ✓ 1 boundary test (min/max edge values, empty strings)
   - For each API field with constraint, generate validation test [IF OpenAPI provided]
   - For each response code, generate contract test [IF OpenAPI provided]
   - [IF NO OpenAPI] Still generate validation tests from acceptance criteria constraints
   - Assign test IDs: TC-<REQ-ID>-<INTENT>
   - Include traceability: sourceIds[], rationale
   - Detect and skip duplicates (normalized key hash)
   
   Key Methods:
   - generate_test_cases(requirements, [optional] api_spec, constraints) -> TestCase[]
   - generate_positive_test(requirement, endpoint) -> TestCase
   - generate_negative_test(requirement, constraint) -> TestCase
   - generate_boundary_test(requirement, constraint) -> TestCase
   - deduplicate_tests(test_cases) -> TestCase[]

4. Test Data Generator
   Input: ApiSpec, Constraint[], TestCase[]
   Output: Payload[], Fixture[]
   
   Responsibilities:
   - Generate constraint-driven mock data (respects type, format, min/max, enum)
   - For positive tests: valid payloads matching all constraints
   - For negative tests: invalid payloads violating one constraint at a time
   - For boundary tests: edge values (min-1, max+1, empty string, etc.)
   - Deterministic PRNG seeded from deterministicSeed
   - Generate request/response examples and fixtures
   
   Key Methods:
   - generate_mock_payload(schema, intent) -> Dict
   - generate_mock_value(field_schema, constraint) -> Any
   - generate_fixtures(test_cases) -> Fixture[]
   - seed_prng(seed) -> Callable

5. Gherkin Generator
   Input: TestCase[], Requirement[]
   Output: .feature files
   
   Responsibilities:
   - Render Gherkin scenarios from test cases
   - Template: Scenario ID + description
   - Given/When/Then steps derived from preconditions, actions, expected results
   - Include tags for intent (positive, negative, boundary, contract)
   - Output: single .feature file or per-endpoint
   
   Key Methods:
   - render_gherkin(test_cases, output_dir) -> None
   - generate_scenario(test_case) -> str
   - generate_given_steps(test_case) -> str[]
   - generate_when_steps(test_case) -> str[]
   - generate_then_steps(test_case) -> str[]

6. Playwright Generator
   Input: TestCase[], ApiSpec, Payload[]
   Output: .spec.ts skeleton files
   
   Responsibilities:
   - Render TypeScript Playwright test skeletons
   - Import @playwright/test
   - For each test case, generate test() block with:
     ✓ setup (auth, base URL)
     ✓ request construction (method, endpoint, headers, body)
     ✓ HTTP call via request.* API
     ✓ assertion placeholder for status + response schema
     ✓ TODO comments for field-level assertions
   - Deterministic file naming: TC-<ID>.spec.ts
   - Include fixture references
   
   Key Methods:
   - render_playwright(test_cases, output_dir) -> None
   - generate_test_function(test_case) -> str
   - generate_request_block(test_case) -> str
   - generate_assertion_block(test_case) -> str
   - generate_fixture_import(test_case) -> str

7. Traceability Matrix Generator
   Input: TestCase[], Requirement[], ApiSpec
   Output: traceability_matrix.json, traceability_matrix.csv
   
   Responsibilities:
   - Create mapping: requirementId → testCaseId → artifactPath
   - Include rationale for each mapping
   - Export as JSON (for tooling) and CSV (for humans)
   - Row schema: requirementId, requirementText, testCaseId, testIntent,
                 artifactPath, rationale
   
   Key Methods:
   - build_traceability_matrix(test_cases, requirements) -> Matrix
   - export_json(matrix, path) -> None
   - export_csv(matrix, path) -> None

8. Basic Coverage Report Generator
   Input: TestCase[], Requirement[], [optional] ApiSpec, Constraint[], ValidationRule[]
   Output: coverage_report.json
   
   Responsibilities:
   - Calculate metrics:
     ✓ acceptanceCriteriaCoverage: percent and list of uncovered criteria [ALWAYS]
     ✓ validationCoverage: percent per-field, overall [ALWAYS]
     ✓ apiCoverage: endpoints covered vs total; status codes covered [CONDITIONAL: if OpenAPI provided]
     ✓ testCaseSummary: total count and breakdown by intent [ALWAYS]
   - Flag any missing coverage (100% target for included metrics)
   - Include `openApiIncluded` boolean flag in report
   - Validate against success criteria (100% of applicable coverage)
   
   Key Methods:
   - build_coverage_report(test_cases, requirements, [optional] api_spec) -> Report
   - calculate_acceptance_coverage(test_cases, requirements) -> Percent
   - calculate_validation_coverage(test_cases, constraints) -> Percent
   - calculate_api_coverage(test_cases, api_spec) -> Percent
   - validate_100_percent_coverage(report) -> bool

==============================================================================
PHASE 2: EXTENSIONS (Weeks 5–8)
==============================================================================

1. JUnit Generator
   Input: TestCase[], ApiSpec, Payload[]
   Output: *Test.java skeleton files
   
   Responsibilities:
   - Render Java JUnit 5 test classes
   - For each test case: @Test method with:
     ✓ @BeforeEach setup (client, auth, base URL)
     ✓ Payload construction
     ✓ HTTP client call (HttpClient or RestTemplate)
     ✓ Status code assertion
     ✓ Response schema assertion (TODO)
   - Fixtures as @ParameterizedTest source
   
   Key Methods:
   - render_junit(test_cases, output_dir) -> None
   - generate_test_class(test_case) -> str
   - generate_test_method(test_case) -> str

2. REST Assured Generator
   Input: TestCase[], ApiSpec, Payload[]
   Output: *Test.java skeleton files (REST Assured fluent API)
   
   Responsibilities:
   - Render Java test classes using RestAssured DSL
   - For each test case:
     ✓ given() setup (headers, auth)
     ✓ when() HTTP call (method, endpoint, body)
     ✓ then() assertions (status, schema validation)
   
   Key Methods:
   - render_rest_assured(test_cases, output_dir) -> None
   - generate_rest_assured_test(test_case) -> str
   - generate_rest_assured_assertions(test_case) -> str

3. Advanced Coverage Analyzer
   Input: TestCase[], Requirement[], ApiSpec
   Output: advanced_coverage.json
   
   Responsibilities:
   - Cross-correlation: requirement interactions, endpoint cascades
   - Gap analysis: identify uncovered scenarios (e.g., auth failures, timeouts)
   - Risk assessment: high-impact uncovered requirements
   - Redundancy detection: test cases testing identical scenarios
   
   Key Methods:
   - analyze_cross_coverage(test_cases, requirements) -> Analysis
   - identify_gaps(requirements, test_cases) -> Gap[]
   - assess_risk(gaps, requirement_priorities) -> RiskMap

4. Regression Impact Analyzer
   Input: TestCase[], Requirement[], new_Requirement[]
   Output: impact_report.json
   
   Responsibilities:
   - Compare old spec vs new spec
   - Identify added, removed, modified requirements
   - Flag test cases that may regress
   - Recommend test case updates or deletions
   
   Key Methods:
   - analyze_spec_diff(old_spec, new_spec) -> Diff
   - impact_on_tests(diff, test_cases) -> ImpactMap
   - recommend_updates(impact_map) -> Recommendation[]

==============================================================================
CORE DATA MODEL
==============================================================================

Requirement
  id: str (AC-001, REQ-ABCD1234)
  text: str
  type: str (acceptance, business_rule, precondition, postcondition)
  actor: str (extracted from "As a <actor>")
  source: str (file path)
  business_rules: str[]
  preconditions: str[]
  postconditions: str[]

ApiSpec
  source: str (file path)
  title: str
  version: str
  endpoints: Endpoint[]

Endpoint
  path: str (/api/users)
  method: str (GET, POST, PUT, PATCH, DELETE)
  summary: str
  description: str
  request: RequestSchema
  responses: Response[]

RequestSchema
  required: bool
  schema: JsonSchema

JsonSchema
  type: str (object, array, string, integer, number, boolean)
  format: str (email, date, uuid, etc.)
  properties: Dict[str, JsonSchema]
  required: str[]
  minLength: int
  maxLength: int
  minimum: int
  maximum: int
  enum: Any[]
  pattern: str (regex)

Response
  status: int (201, 400, 409)
  description: str
  schema: JsonSchema

Constraint
  field: str
  type: str
  rules: Dict[str, Any]  # { minLength, required, enum, pattern, ... }

TestCase
  id: str (TC-AC-001-POS)
  sourceIds: str[] (AC-001, AC-002)
  description: str
  intent: str (positive, negative, boundary, validation, contract)
  type: str (functional, validation, api, boundary)
  request_example: Dict
  expected_status: int
  expected_response_schema: JsonSchema (optional)
  rationale: str (why this test is important)
  endpoint: Endpoint (optional)
  tags: str[]

Fixture
  test_case_id: str
  request_payload: Dict
  expected_response: Dict (optional)
  headers: Dict[str, str]
  auth_token: str (optional, masked)

TraceabilityRecord
  requirement_id: str
  requirement_text: str
  test_case_id: str
  test_intent: str
  artifact_path: str
  rationale: str

CoverageReport
  acceptance_criteria_coverage: { total, covered, percent, uncovered }
  validation_coverage: { total_rules, covered_rules, percent, by_field }
  api_coverage: { total_endpoints, covered_endpoints, percent, status_codes_covered }
  test_case_summary: { total, by_intent: { positive, negative, boundary, contract, validation } }

GenerationManifest
  generator_version: str
  generated_at: str (ISO 8601)
  deterministic_seed: str (SHA256 of canonicalized sources)
  sources: { path, checksum }[]
  test_cases: { id, source_ids, checksum }[]
  artifacts: { path, type, checksum }[]

