==============================================================================
SKILL INTERACTION FLOW
==============================================================================

Phase 1: File-Based Generator

User creates or edits:
  ├─ examples/user-story.md
  ├─ examples/api-spec.yaml
  └─ examples/validation-rules.yaml

User runs:
  python run_generation.py

Generator flow:
  1. Load config.yaml
  2. Parse inputs:
     ├─ RequirementAnalyzer.parse(user-story.md) → Requirement[]
     ├─ ApiContractAnalyzer.parse(api-spec.yaml) → ApiSpec
     └─ ValidationRuleAnalyzer.parse(validation-rules.yaml) → Constraint[]
  3. Normalize & validate:
     ├─ Canonicalize requirement IDs
     ├─ Dereference OpenAPI $ref
     └─ Extract field constraints
  4. Generate test cases:
     └─ TestDesignGenerator.generate(requirements, api_spec, constraints) → TestCase[]
  5. Generate test data:
     └─ TestDataGenerator.generate(test_cases, constraints) → Fixture[]
  6. Build traceability & coverage:
     ├─ TraceabilityMatrixGenerator.build() → Matrix
     └─ CoverageReportGenerator.build() → Report
  7. Render output artifacts:
     ├─ GherkinAdapter.render(test_cases) → .feature files
     ├─ PlaywrightAdapter.render(test_cases) → .spec.ts files
     └─ JsonExporter.render(manifest, matrix, report) → .json files
  8. Write manifest & validate 100% coverage

Output structure:
  output/<timestamp>/
  ├─ manifest.json              (deterministic seed, checksums)
  ├─ intermediate_model.json    (parsed & normalized)
  ├─ coverage_report.json       (acceptance, validation, API %)
  ├─ gaps.json                  (missing/ambiguous requirements)
  ├─ traceability_matrix.json   (test → requirement mapping)
  ├─ gherkin/
  │   └─ generated_tests.feature
  └─ playwright/
      └─ *.spec.ts

Phase 2: Enhanced Workflows (Future)
  - HTTP API for /generate endpoint
  - CLI with --formats, --watch, --diff flags
  - Gradle/Maven plugin integration
  - VS Code extension for in-editor preview
  - Git diff analysis (old spec → new spec impact)

