==============================================================================
RISK ASSESSMENT
==============================================================================

Risk: OpenAPI spec contains unresolved $ref
  Severity: High
  Mitigation: Dereference $ref before schema extraction; flag unresolved refs in gaps.json
  
Risk: Acceptance criteria are ambiguous or incomplete
  Severity: High
  Mitigation: Flag ambiguous language; generate stubs; document in gaps.json
  
Risk: Generated test data violates business logic (semantic errors)
  Severity: Medium
  Mitigation: Constraint-driven mock generation reduces but doesn't eliminate risk;
              include TODO comments in test skeletons for manual validation
  
Risk: Playwright/JUnit templates become outdated with framework versions
  Severity: Medium
  Mitigation: Version templates; provide upgrade path; document template changes
  
Risk: Generator becomes non-deterministic
  Severity: Critical
  Mitigation: Strong canonicalization; SHA256-based deterministic seed;
              integration tests verify identical runs produce identical checksums
  
Risk: Hallucinated fields or endpoints
  Severity: Critical
  Mitigation: Anti-hallucination checks in generator; flag missing data;
              strict adherence to specification; unit tests for boundary cases

==============================================================================
TESTING STRATEGY
==============================================================================

Unit Tests (Week 2–4)
  ✓ Each parser: test against valid/invalid inputs, edge cases
  ✓ Each generator: test with various requirement/constraint combinations
  ✓ Canonicalization: verify deterministic output
  ✓ Mock data: verify generated payloads match constraints
  ✓ Adapters: verify generated code syntax is valid (static check)

Integration Tests (Week 4)
  ✓ Full flow: user story → acceptance criteria → test cases → Gherkin → artifact
  ✓ Determinism: run twice, compare output checksums
  ✓ Coverage validation: 100% acceptance, validation, API coverage
  ✓ Traceability: every test maps to at least one requirement
  ✓ Anti-hallucination: no invented fields or endpoints

Regression Tests (Week 5+)
  ✓ Sample fixtures (test files) locked; re-run generator; verify no regressions
  ✓ Version compatibility: old specs still work with new generator
  ✓ Performance: generator completes within SLA (e.g., < 5s for typical spec)

Manual QA (Throughout)
  ✓ Review generated Gherkin scenarios for readability
  ✓ Review generated Playwright skeletons for compile errors
  ✓ Verify Traceability matrix is complete and accurate
  ✓ Verify Coverage report metrics are correct

==============================================================================
SUCCESS CRITERIA (Phase 1)
==============================================================================

Functional
  ✓ 100% acceptance criteria coverage (or documented gaps)
  ✓ 100% validation rule coverage (or documented gaps)
  ✓ 100% API endpoint coverage (or documented gaps)
  ✓ Deterministic output: identical inputs → identical outputs
  ✓ Every test case traces back to at least one requirement
  ✓ No hallucinated fields, endpoints, or constraints
  ✓ Gherkin scenarios are syntactically valid
  ✓ Playwright skeletons compile without errors

Non-functional
  ✓ Generation completes in < 5 seconds for typical spec (< 50 endpoints)
  ✓ All critical code paths covered by unit tests (>90% coverage)
  ✓ Manifest.json is valid JSON and includes all required fields
  ✓ Documentation is complete and includes examples

Governance
  ✓ Constitution principles honored: specification-first, deterministic, traceable
  ✓ All design goals met: modular, extensible, framework-agnostic
  ✓ Code adheres to Python style (PEP 8)

